      {
        "id": 3862711,
        "name": "Alexander Gillette ",
        "username": "A_Gillette",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/da6949/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-08-07T18:47:15.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"284668\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>This assumes corks are responsible for premox.<br>\nThat leaves a lot of other possibilities out.<br>\nAnd, in the absence of proof that it is always the corks, I am unconvinced.<br>\nBest, Jim</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Actually, if you read it, you will see that it is predicated on a theory that there are multiple causes of premox, not just the cork.<br>\nAlex</p>",
